definitions.definition: ( entomology ) Synonym of teneral ( “ an insect or other arthropod such as a spider which has just undergone ecdysis ( “ shedding of the exoskeleton ” ) and so lacks colour or firmness ” ) .
( UK , regional , mining , archaic ) The upper layer of rubble in a quarry which has to be removed to reach the material to be mined .

subdefinitions.definition: ( ornithology ) A young bird which has not developed feathers yet; a nestling . ( figurative ) A person lacking life experience ; an immature or naive person.
( East Anglia ) Synonym of topsoil ( “ upper layer of soil ” ) .

main_definition: ( entomology ) Synonym of teneral ( “ an insect or other arthropod such as a spider which has just undergone ecdysis ( “ shedding of the exoskeleton ” ) and so lacks colour or firmness ” ) .
secondary_definitions: ( UK , regional , mining , archaic ) The upper layer of rubble in a quarry which has to be removed to reach the material to be mined .

definitions.definition: A low-lying meadow near a river which is regularly submerged .

main_definition: ( Ireland ) A low-lying meadow near a river which is regularly submerged .
